Create a class Gadget with the below attributes:

modelNumber - int

stock - int

type - String

brand - String

Write getters, setters, and a parameterized constructor in the above-mentioned attribute sequence as required.

📘 Solution Class Requirements
Create a class Solution with the main method.

Implement two static methods:

countTotalStockForType

findGadgetByBrandAndModel

📘 Method Descriptions
1. countTotalStockForType(Gadget[] gadgets, String type):
Takes an array of Gadget objects and a String parameter type.

Returns the total stock of gadgets that match the given type.

If no gadgets of the given type are found, return 0.

2. findGadgetByBrandAndModel(Gadget[] gadgets, String brand, int modelNumber):
Takes three parameters:

an array of Gadget objects

a String brand

an int modelNumber

Returns the Gadget object that matches both brand and modelNumber.

If either condition is not met, return null.

📘 Main Method Tasks
Take input and call countTotalStockForType.

Print the total stock if found.
Else print:
No Gadget found with mentioned attribute.
Take input and call findGadgetByBrandAndModel.
If result is not null, print:
No Gadget found with mentioned attribute.

All methods should be called from the main method.

